  "text": "In conclusion, regardless of the underlying reason for the different results, our reporter data and SNP analyses, presented here and previously, demonstrate that head-on genes undergo accelerated evolution independently of sequence context-based effects [CITATION_1] . Therefore, the established activities of TC-NER and PolY1 appear sufficient to explain this process.",
